HEADWORD: Madreporaria
<hw>Mad`re*po*ra"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Madrepore</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An extensive
division of Anthozoa, including most of the species that produce stony
corals. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Anthozoa</er>.</def> --
